article.headline: Long Beach State 38, Indiana State 37
article.story: HONOLULU (AP) -- Shawn Hawkins' putback with 0.8 seconds remaining lifted Long Beach State to a 38-37 win over Indiana State in the seventh-place game of the Rainbow Classic Thursday afternoon. Hawkins' shot under the basket came after Cody Pearson drove to the basket along the left baseline and missed. After a time-out, Indiana State could not get off a shot as both teams broke the 39-year-old tournament record of 41 for fewest points scored and set the record for the lowest scoring game in the tournament's 41-year history. Hawkins led Long Beach State (2-7) with 14 points while David Moss scored 10 for Indiana State (5-6). Indiana State took a 37-33 lead with 1:34 remaining on Moss jumper from the free throw line. Jibril Hodges 3-pointer cut the lead to 37-36 and the Sycamores turned the ball over on the next possession. Long Beach State shot 35 percent from the field (17-of-49) while the Sycamores made just 14-of-56 shots (25 percent).
